  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>A thin, ragged man stands waiting on the barge, leaning on the oar. A smile of greeting splits his weathered features.

"It has been a very long time since an outsider sought passage to the Burial Isle." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Take me across." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What is this Burial Isle?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Is it dangerous?" </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Leave] "Farewell." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>"It is a sacred place, for it sits upon the great works of the Builders. There, by our ancestors, all our anamfaths are laid to rest. Few go there, my friend. It is not a place where the living to walk."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>Dorvhal greets you with the same quiet smile. "Have you finished your business here?" </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>Dorvhal inclines his head in acknowledgment. "I will. Take care that you do not lose your footing. These waters have a fickle temper." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>Dorvhal nods solemnly. "Those I bring to the island return the same way, or else not at all. It is home only to the dead. Spirits - shades - of the Builders remain, and watch over our anamfatha. They are bound to the island, and protect it fiercely."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm ready to return to Oldsong."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What do you know of the temple on the island?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Come, then. I will take us back." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>Dorvhal's lined face turns up toward the rest of the island, then back to you. "That is the Court of the Penitents. It is a dreaded place - and one to be respected. As the gods must sometimes be feared, but always obeyed."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
</StringTableFile>